    "updates": [
        {
            "version": "2.0.1",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>Update!<\/strong> Stacks 2 Update.<\/li><li><strong>Update!<\/strong> Cleaned up stack attributes, urls, etc.<\/li><li><strong>Update!<\/strong> Added to Joe Workman group in S2.<\/li><\/ol><p>This update will still allow the stack to function in Stacks v1.4<\/p>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.0.2",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>Fixed!<\/strong> Removed \u201cFancy Image\u201d from stack name.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.0.3",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>Update!<\/strong> Added titles for Stacks 2.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.0.4",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>Fixed!<\/strong> This update fixes Stacks v2.1 compatibility. This is <strong><em>my fault<\/em><\/strong> for being overzealous with the API. Its nothing that YourHead has changed. Sorry.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.0",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>New<\/strong> Updated for and requires Stacks 2.<\/li><li><strong>New<\/strong> Auto rotation settings.<\/li><li><strong>New<\/strong> Keyboard navigation for dektop.<\/li><li><strong>New<\/strong> Swipe navigation for touch devices. The image can also be tapped to trigger rotation.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.1",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>New<\/strong> New icon.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.10",
            "date": "2015-08-13T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ul><li>Updated tags for better organization in Stacks 3 library<\/li><li>New icons for Stacks 3 library<\/li><\/ul>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.2",
            "date": "2012-12-01T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li><strong>Fix<\/strong> When using Click and Drag, and the mouseup event now triggers on both the image and the parent stack. This will stop the animation from working on mouse over.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.3",
            "date": "2012-12-13T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li>All JW stacks have taken a diet. They are all leaner and meaner. This will provide you with faster page download times. Enjoy!<\/li><li>Other small fixes and enhancements may apply\u2026<\/li><li>We\u2019ve been quiet for a few months. That can mean only one thing, watch out for 2013. Big things are coming!<\/li><li>Happy Holidays from Joe, Rob and Tron<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.4",
            "date": "2012-12-14T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li>All JW stacks have taken a diet. They are all leaner and meaner. This will provide you with faster page download times. Enjoy!<\/li><li>Other small fixes and enhancements may apply<\/li><li>We have been quiet for a few months. That can mean only one thing, watch out for 2013. Big things are coming!<\/li><li>Happy Holidays from Joe, Rob and Tron<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.5",
            "date": "2013-02-22T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li>Made the setting for the number of images a number box. This will remove any confusion about using the slider to get the exact number that you want.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.6",
            "date": "2013-03-07T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li>Added the \u2018threesixty\u2019 class to the 360 images. This will allow for more flexible custom styling for all you CSS geeks out there.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.7",
            "date": "2013-08-02T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ol><li>Increased the number of images allowed to 200.<\/li><\/ol>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.8",
            "date": "2014-09-22T00:00:00+00:00",
            "notes": "<ul><li>Removed all comments from code<\/li><li>New meta tags for stack version tracking<\/li><li>Getting ready for <strong>**<\/strong><strong>**<\/strong> launch<\/li><\/ul>"
        },
        {
            "version": "2.1.9",
            "date": "2015-08-02T00:00:00+00:00",
